The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umahannon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mahannon </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/29/01 10:45:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please Read-Your views on Wizards</span><hr size=1> Despite all of the setbacks wizards have experienced since the release of Kunark and Velious, I still think they are a powerful and useful class if played strategically.  When used just as the &quot;big gun&quot; they aren't all that useful, but if the wizard in question knows which spells to cast in a given situation and more importantly when to cast them they are a good addition to a group.  This is not to say they couldn't use some tweaking.  In regard to Velious mobs, the total mob HP to total damage per bar of wizard mana ratio is way out of whack, and it's only somewhat ameliorated by the Bane spells, which are only available at level 60.  They either need a boost in efficiency, or a suite of non-damage spells that are beneficial to have in a group.  There is a bard song that causes a mob to be gated to it's bind with an aggro wipe, why this wasn't given to wizards in spell form is beyond me.<br>
<br>
Altogether wizards rank at around 7.5 in my opinion, a good class, but one in need of tweaking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ularladorplaneswalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Larlador Planeswalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/30/01 12:14:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please Read-Your views on Wizards</span><hr size=1> Two of my best friends are wizards, both lvl 51. I'd group with an wizard anytime i can, given they know their class well (my friends play em right). An wizard who knows what he's doing, is an potential lifesaver to any group and great to have for camp breakins where there are multible mobs to nuke down with IC when the mob is in his last 2 bubs.<br>
